The paper proposes a framework for data-driven pricing in shared vehicle systems, which involves optimization and algorithmic techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics), which deals with the mathematical modeling of strategic interactions between agents. The paper also uses data-driven approaches and closed queueing models, which are common in machine learning and data analysis, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper deals with optimization under constraints, which is a topic in cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
